<item>
            <title>[SPARK-4812] SparkPlan.codegenEnabled may be initialized to a wrong value</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-4812</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The problem is `codegenEnabled` is `val`, but it uses a `val` `sqlContext`, which can be override by subclasses. Here is a simple example to show this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;scala&amp;gt; :paste
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Entering paste mode (ctrl-D to finish)
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;abstract&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo {

  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;protected&lt;/span&gt; val sqlContext = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Foo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;

  val codegenEnabled: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Boolean&lt;/span&gt; = {
    println(sqlContext) &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// it will call subclass&apos;s `sqlContext` which has not yet been initialized.
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (sqlContext != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
    } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;
    }
  }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Bar &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; Foo {
  override val sqlContext = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Bar&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
}

println(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Bar().codegenEnabled)

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Exiting paste mode, now interpreting.
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;
defined &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo
defined &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Bar

scala&amp;gt; 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should make `sqlContext` `final` to prevent subclasses from overriding it incorrectly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
